6 94\nDetroit Edison 5s \u201949 105%\nDetroit Edison col 5s \u201833 102\nDuquesne Light 4%s \u201967 103\nErie Ry 6s 77\nFlorida East Coast 5s \u201974 20\nGeneral Motors Accept 6s \u201937.... 102\nGreat Northern 4%5; 96%\nHud. Manhattan inc 5s '57.... 74\nHudson Coal 5s \u201962 53%\nHumble Oil 5%s \u201932 102\nInland Steel 4%s \u20197B 95%\nInter Rapid Transit 7s \u201932 88\nInt Tel A Tel 4%s cv 79%\nLackawanpa Steel 5\u00ab A \u2019SO 100%\nLaclede Gas 5s \u201934 fd 101%\nMidvale Steel 5s \u201936 100%\nMissouri Pacific 4s \u201975 69%\nMissouri Pacific 5s \u201965 95\nMissouri Pacific 5s F \u201967 95%\nMorris A Co 4%s \u201939 79%\nNat Dairy Prod 5%s \u20194B 98%\nN E Tel A Tel 4%s \u20196l 103\nN Y Chi St L 4%s 87%\nNY NH A H 6s \u20194O 114%\nNY NH A H 6s \u20194B 114%\nNiagara Falls Power 6s 102%\nNorfolk A Western 4s \u201996 97%\nNorth Amer Edison 5s 96%\nOtis Steel 6s \u20194l 96\nPacific Gas A El 5s \u201942 102%\nParam\u2019nt Laskv Famous 65.*.., 92\nPa the Exchange 7s \u201937 50\nPennsylvania 4%s \u201965 100%\nPennsylvania 4%s \u20196O 95%\nPennsylvania 5s \u201864 103\nPennsylvania 5s \u2019BB 105%\nPennsylvania B%s \u201936 108%\nSEABOARD GETS\nRECEIVERSHIP\nNORFOLK, Va\u201e Dec. 24 (1.N.5.)\nActing on the petition of the\nBethlehem Steel Company, Fed\neral Judge D. Lawrence Groner\nappointed as equity receivers for\nthe Seaboard Air Line Railway,\nL. R. Powell, Jr., president of the\nrailway, and Ethelbert W. Smith,\na vice president of the Pennsyl\nvania Railroad, who began their\nduties today.\nThe steel company alleged in a\nbill of complaint that the railway\nwas indebted to it in the sum\nof $234,481.98. The bill also al\nleged that railway had to meet\nheavy loan payments and inter\nest on more than $1,000,000 with\nin the next few weeks and that\nno funds were available.\nAccording to a statement filed\nwith the bill, the funded debt of\nthe railway in the hands of the\npublic totals $215,695,301.84.\nThe receivers took over active\ncontrol of the railway with full\npower to operate it to the best\nadvantage of all creditors. All\nclaims against the company must\nbe filed with receivers within\nthree months.\nW. R. C. Cocke, general coun\nsel for the railway, announced\nthere would be no change in\npersonnel, no cut in employes in\nany community and that the\nroad would function as usual.\nBaltimore and Ohio\nGets Time Extension\nThe Interstate Commerce Com\nmission today extended from\nJanuary 13 to June 13, 1931, the\neffective date of its order requir\ning the Baltimore and Ohio Rail\nroad to divest itself of its capi\ntal stock holding in the Western\nMaryland Railway Co.\nThis is the second extension\nthe road has received.\nHarper, Dean of Bankers,\nOnce a Local Druggist\nCol. Robert N. Harper, dean\nemeritus of the banking profes\nsion in Washington, was formerly\na druggist. Colonel Harper is the\nsj \"1\nHr\nWF*-?. xh\nW\nW,'\nI\nROBERT N. HARPER\nretired president of the District\nNational Bank, where, for many\nyears, he served as a leading light\nin financial circle*.\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\nPhiladelphia Co 5\u00ab \u201967 98\nPhila El Power 4%s \u2019B7 101%\nPub Ser G A El 6\u00ab '67 103%\nPure Oil 5%a \u201937 \u00bb0\nPuritv Baking 6a \u20194B 90%\nSt L A San Fran 4\u00bb A \u2019SO 85%\nSt L A San Francisco 4%k \u201973.. 77%\nSeaboard Air Line 6a A \u201945 14%\nSeaboard Air L Fla Is A \u201936.. 9%\nShell Union Oil 5a \u201947 w* 82\nSinclair OU 6%a B \u20193B 95\nSinclair Oil 7a A \u201937 76\nSinclair Crude OU 5%a \u20193B 100%\nSinclair Pipe Line 5s \u201943 99%\nSouthern Pacific 4%s 95%\nStandard 011 N Y 4%s \u20196l 97%\nS W Bell Tel 5s \u201964 104%\nTexas Corp 5a \u201944 99%\nTexas A Pacific 6a C *79 99%\nUnited Drug 5s *53 96\nU S Rubber 5s \u201947 69%\nVertientes Sugar 7s '43 40\nWabash Ry 5\" B *76 92\nWabash Ry 5%s \u201975 93\nWestern Maryland 5%s \u201977....... 93%\nWestern Union 5s \u2019BO 102%\nWestern Union 6%s \u201936 108\nWhite Sewing Machine 6s \u20193B xw. 29%\nWilson A Co 6s \u20194l 98%\nYoungstown S A T 5s A \u20197B 102\nForeign Bonds\nArgentine 6s A \u201957 91\nAustria 7s \u201953 103%\nAustralia 5s \u201957 72\nAustralia 5s \u201955 73\nBelgium 7s \u201956 107%\nBolivia 7s 'SB M\nBolivia 8s \u201947 44\nBrazil 6%s \u201926 57\nBrazil 7s '52 57\nCanada 5s \u201952 104\nChlfe 6s \u201962 Mar 75%\nChinese Gov Ry 6s \u20196l 26%\n.Danish Mun Loan 8s A *46 107%\nDenmark 4%s 94\nFinland 6%s 89\nFinland 7s \u2019SO 94\nFrench 7%s 125%\nFrench Gov 7s I\u2019o\nGerman Bank 6s July 69\nGerman Rep 5%s 71%\nGreek Is 52%\nItaly 7s 92%\nJapanese 5%s 92\nJapanese 6%s 102%\nMilan 6%s 75\nNord Ry 6%s 184%\nNorway 5%s 101%\nNorway 6s 105\nOslo Gas 95%\nParis Lyons A Med 6s 104%\nRome ..%s 79\nSao Paulo State 8s 86\nSaxon Public Works B%s 74\nSaxon Public Works 7s 78%\nSeine Department 7s 106%\nSerbia 7s 78%\nSwiss Confederation 5%s 105\nToho Electric 6s 96%\nTokyo Elec Light 6 s 82%\nTokyo 5%s 87%\nUruguay 8s 99%\nYokohama 6s 95%\n\u25a0MERGER PLANS\nHELD UP\nNEW YORK, Dec. 24. \u2014The\nconference between executives of\nthe Eastern railroads held today\nwas adjourned without reaching\nany definite decision regarding\n1 the establishment of four major\ntrunk-line systems in the East,\n1 it is announced. It also was\nstated that the meetings would\nprobably be resumed within the\nnext fortnight.\nAmong those attending the\nconference were O. P. and M. J.\nVan Sweringen, of the Nickel\nPlate system; Patrick Crowley\nand A. H. Harris, of the New\nYork Central; W. W. Atterbury\nand Elisha Lee, of the Pennsyl-\nvania, and Daniel Willard and\nGeorge M. Shriver, of the Balti\nmore and Ohio.\nI It was reported that some\nprogress had been made.\nSeveral proposals were dis-\ncussed, but they all hinged on\ni the final disposition of the\nI Wabash and the Lehigh Valley\nby the Pennsylvania. The Penn\nl sylvania, it is understood, is will\ning to relinquish control of both\n1 of those roads if it could make\nsatisfactory trackage arrange\nments with the -Nickel Plate.\nI Thus far, efforts have been\nblocked by the Pennsylvania, ac\ncording to the other systems.\nIt is understood, however, that\nthe latter road is taking a more\nfriendly attitude towards the\ndiscussions.\nB. O, Must Sell\nW. Maryland Stock\nThe Baltimore and Ohio rail\nway was yesterday given until\nJune 13 to divest itself of its\ncapital stock holdings in the\nWestern Maryland Railroad Co.\nThe extension of time was\ngranted by the Interstate Com\nmerce Commission.\nWW\ni In olden days, when Made\u2019s\nHotel and the Metropolitan were\nfavorite gathering places for the\n1 elite of the city. Colonel Harper\nestablished his pharmacy in the\nold Metropolitan.\nStatesmen, who had dined none\ntoo wisely on the champagne sup\nper of the era, often dropped into\nthe store of the youthful druggist\nfor first aid to terrific hangovers.\nThe colonel entered the finan\ncial field here in 1903 when he or\nganized the American National\nBank. In. 1909, he became presi\ndent of the District National and\nmaintained that position until\nhis retirement.\nBom in Virginia, Colonel\nHarper always claims he is a\nWashingtonian and, to a degree,\nhe Is, for he has lived here for\nmore than 50 years.\nNew Oil Markets\nFound, Says Wilbur\nSecretary of the Interior Wil\nbur, chairman of the Federal\noil conservation board, reported\nto President Hoover today that\nhe believed the board has per\nfeced a plan that will prevent\nthe 10,000 or so Independent oil\nproducers in Kansas and Okla\nhoma from closing their wells\nJanuary 1. Mr. Wilbur said:\n\u201cWe\u2019re finding new markets\nfor the oil, and by using the\npipe lines of other companies\nwe believe the situation will be\ncleared by January V\nFALSE REPORTS\nBLAMED IN N. Y.\nBANK CLOSING\nMore Institutions in South\nShut After Withdrawals;\nState Examiner Quits Post\nNEW YORK, Dec. 24. \u2014The\nChelsea Bank and Trust Company\nand its assets were taken over by\nState Superintendent of Banks\nJoseph A. Broderick yesterday.\nHeavy withdrawals by deposit\nors attributed to false and mali\ncious rumors concerning the com\npany\u2019s financial affairs prompted\nthe action, Broderick said.\nThe bank is not a member of\nthe New York Clearing House\nAssociation and not a member of\nthe Federal Reserve System, al\nthough it has access to Federal\nReserve funds through its cor\nrespondent banks.\nBank Examiner Quits\nAfter $8,000,000 Theft\nSACRAMENTO, Calif., Dec. 28\n(1.N.5.) .\u2014Gov. C. C. Young yester\nday accepted the resignation of\nCharles A. Whitmore, State build\ning and loan commissioner, to\ntake effect January 6. Whitmore\nhas been criticized by Governor\nelect James Rolph, Jr., who will\nbe inaugurated on January 6, be\ncause his office did not discover\nthe $8,000,000 defalcations of\nG. H. Beesemyer in the Holly\nwood Guaranty Building and Loan\nAssociation.\nBessemer (Ala.) Banks\nClosed by Directors\nBESSEMER. Ala., Dec. 24\n(1.N.5.) .\u2014The City National Bank\nand the Bessemer Trust and\nSavings Bank failed to open here\nyesterday.\nThe Bessemer Trust and Sav\nings Bank had a capital of $60,-\n000 and deposits of $442,660, ac\ncording to its last periodical re\nport.\nThe City National Bank had a\ncapital of SIOO,OOO and deposits of\n$800,160.\nWashington (Ga.) Bank\nFails to Open Doors\nWASHINGTON, Ga., Dec. 24\n(I.N.S.),\u2014The National Bank\nof Wilkes failed to open here yes\nterday. The bank was capitalized\nat $50,000. According to its last\nreport, it had a surplus of $70,000\nand resources of $400,000.\nBALTIMORE LIVE STOCK\nBALTIMORE. Dec. 24.\u2014Live stock:\nCattle \u2014Receipts, 15 head; market\nzteadv. Stock yards will be closed\nChristmas. Steers \u2014Medium to grood. 39\n\u00ab5>10.50; fair to medium, 87.50@8.50;\nplain to fair. 3607.26: common to\nplain, 85 @6. Bulls, medium to good,\n$5.50@6; fair to medium. 3505.50;\nplain to fair. 34.50035; common to\nplain. 3404.50. Cows, good to choice.\n35.5006; medium to good, 34.7505.26;\nfair to medium. 8404.50; plain to fair,\n3304; common to plain. 3*03. Helfers,\ngood to choice. 38.2508.75; medium to\ngood. 37.2508.26; fair to medium., 36.25\n07.25; plain to fair. 86.75@6.25; com\nmon to plain. 84.50 05.50. Fresh cows\nand springers. 840080.\nSheep and Lambs\u2014 Receipts, 100 head;\nmarket steady. Sheep, 31.500 4; lambs,\n84.5009.25.\nHogs\u2014Receirts, 150 head: market\nsteady. Lights. 38.90 0 9.15; heavies,\n88.2508.75; medium. 38.9009.15;\n86.7507.70; light pigs, 88.7509; pigs,\n88.9009.15. Ohio hoga 19 to 15 cents\nhigher than quotation*.\nCalves\u2014Receipts. 25 bead; market\nsteady, calves. 35012.\nBALTIMORE SECURITIES\nI N,t\nSTOCKS |Cloee|Chge\nArundel Corporation 37%\nAtl. Coast Lins RR.._\u00bb.. 99%\nBaltimore Trust 30\nBlack A Decker 10\nCom Credit bt B 20%\nCons GEL Power 82\nCons G E L A P 6% pf 102%\nConsolidation Coal 1%\nEastern Rolling Mills 7\nFidelity A Deposit 128 \u20142\nFidelity A Guar Fire 24\nMfrs Finance vt 3\nMan Finance Ist pf......... 10\nMan Finance 2dpf 3%\nMaryland Casualty..... 25 \u2014l%\nMaryland Trust 31\nMer A Miners Tr Co 33%\nMonongah Pw 7% pt....... 24%\nUnion Trust 52\nU S Fidelity A Guar 25%\nBONDS\nBalto City 4s \u20196l SL 99%\nConsolidation Coal 5s 25 \u2014I\nLake Roland 6s 80 \u20141\nUn Rys A Elec Ist 4s 44\nUn Rys A Elec Income 45.. 20\nUn Rys A Elec fdg 6s 39 \u20141\nHotels and Resorts\nNEW YORK. Ji. I.\nTRAVELING\nat th* flmi'i expanse or \"on your own\u2019\nyou can save at the Hotel Lincoln and still\nENJOY THE BEST\n100% of the 1400 rooms and baths at\nthe new Hotel Lincoln are priced at\n13, $3 JO, $4, $5, for one\ns4\u2014s7 for two\nB NEW YOU ICS MEW\nSHF A.W.BAYUTTC II -f- f- I\nMssgpss Mreeter 1] ILL\nLINCOLN\nEIGHTH AVENUE, 44th to 45th STREETS, TIMES SQUARE\nTA\u00ab National Daily\nI N. Curb Market\nHtghl Low Last\nAcms Steel 38% 83% 83%\nAlum Co of Am 163 IIS 111%\nAm Comnw A 11% 11 11%\nAm Cyanam B 1% 1% 1%\nAm Dept Store 1% 1% 1%\nAm Equities 4% 4% 4%\nAm Fou